      "writtenOn": "2020-12-08T15:38:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the core of the idea is in needMoreBytes, and innerMake. The nice part is that I sync the alignment of fCapacity to be aligned with the raw data pointer fBytes. This allows most of the difficult calculation to be in ptrdiff_t space (the type of fCapacity) instead of pointer space. \n\nI do understand your point with keeping SkArenaAlloc, and I think that most of the ideas can be moved over, but it will still be much more complicated than SkArena. The idea of handing out destructor pointers can be fully implemented in SkAreanAlloc, and will make for faster allocations, and I do intend to move these ideas over.\n\nTo me there is some benefit of having the two systems. When I use SkArena, I\u0027m responsible for destroying the objects. When I use SkArenaAlloc, everything is taken care of for me.",
      "parentUuid": "e6215944_df72fef8",
      "revId": "ba51c314f753482191353d0bf7c84fbef8aa1cf2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
