      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T23:22:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We do very much rely today on objects in SkArenaAlloc outliving their scope and being destroyed at a point that higher-level code decides is appropriate.\n\nBut can\u0027t we add your new capability transparently to SkArenaAlloc using makeBytesAlignedTo()?  Something like,\n\n    template \u003ctypename T, typename... Args\u003e\n    auto makeUnique(Args\u0026\u0026... args) {\n        void* ptr \u003d this-\u003emakeBytesAlignedTo(sizeof(T), alignof(T));\n        T* typed \u003d new (ptr) T(std::forward\u003cArgs\u003e(args)...);\n\n        auto dtor \u003d [](T* p) { p-\u003e~T(); };\n        return std::unique_ptr\u003cT, decltype(dtor)\u003e{typed};\n    }\n\nNo footer there right?",
      "range": {
